# UJL Clean Code: Comments and TODOs

## Goal

Comments should capture intent and constraints, not restate obvious code.

## Must

- English only in comments and TODOs.
- Explain WHY, trade-offs, invariants, or non-obvious constraints.
- Keep TODOs actionable with reason and, if possible, a reference (issue/PR/task).
- Remove stale comments when code changes.

## Should

- Prefer clearer code over explanatory comments.
- Keep comments short and close to the relevant line/block.

## Avoid

- Step-by-step narration of obvious operations.
- Change-history notes in code comments.
- Emojis in code comments and technical docs.

## Allowed Exceptions

- Short section comments in complex algorithms where structure is not obvious.
- Temporary migration notes with clear removal intent.
